<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1590.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-11-15"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 15, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatch of the 2d of
                            June last, No. 973, which is accompanied by a copy of the correspondence
                            between yourself and Earl Russell <pb facs="0701" n="661" xml:id="pg_661"/> on the occasion of communicating to his lordship a
                            copy of the President’s proclamation of the 10th of May in regard to
                            insurgent cruisers.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>